<section>
  <title><literal>Usage</literal> object type</title>
  <para> An indication of some restriction on the use of the lexical item such time (old-fashioned,
    neologism), region (dialect), register (formal, colloquial), domain (medicine, politics) or
    grammar (singular-only).</para>
  <para>
    Child of:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>Entry</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>Sense</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>Pronunciation</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>InflectedForm</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    Properties:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>value</literal> (non-empty string) </para>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para>Can be constrained and mapped to external authorities by the DMLex Controlled Vocabularies Module.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>listingOrder</literal>
      </para>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para> Can be implicit from the serialization.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <example>
    <title>Example of a usage label</title>
    <programlisting>Entry: headword="bitch"
    Sense: definition="a female dog"
    Sense: definition="a woman who is difficult to get along with"
        Usage: value="slang"</programlisting>
  </example>
</section>
